Judul: Space telescope faces cuts: NASA takes a hard look at capabilities of planned dark-energy probe as costs rise.
Abstrak:
NASA’s next major space observatory is meant to tackle some of the biggest questions in astronomy when it
launches in 2025 — including what exoplanets look like and how dark energy is driving the Universe’s expansion. But the project’s cost is rising quickly, and NASA managers are struggling to keep its budget in check.
Fakultas: Fakultas Matematika dan Ilmu Pengetahuan Alam
